<p>
<seg id=1> Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, who is now visiting the United States of America, spoke on Sino-US relations at a joint press conference with US Secretary of State Albright on 29th in Washington D. C.. </seg>
<seg id=2> Tang Jiaxuan also said that the sex scandal of President Clinton was an internal affair of the US, and China would not ever forget the contributions by President Clinton in promoting Sino-US friendship. </seg>
<seg id=3> Now it is reported by VOA reporter Zhou Youkang from the press conference. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Fellow audiences, US President Clinton met at the White House with visiting Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan in Washington D. C., at 11:30 on the morning of 29th. </seg>
<seg id=5> On the noon of 29th, US Secretary of State Albright announced at the joint press conference with Tang held in the State Department that President Clinton had met with Tang. </seg>
<seg id=6> Albright said, </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> "I am very pleased to tell you that President Clinton has just met with Forign Minister Tang, and China has decided to sign on the International Convention on Civil Rights and Political Rights on October 5th in New York." said Secretary of State Albright </seg>
<seg id=8> Tang Jiaxuan, Foreign Minister of China indicated as well at the press conference that it was of profound significance to meet President Clinton. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> "President Clinton met with me and I think our meeting was successful." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> President Clinton is now at troubled times and many people inside and outside the United States expressed their strong resentment and criticism because of his sex scandal. </seg>
<seg id=11> Someone suggested to impeach him, someone requested him to resign, and some Democratic congressmen even made a clean breakaway with him." </seg>
<seg id=12> However, Tang was not evasive at all. He greatly praised and commended President Clinton for his contributions in promoting Sino-US relations. </seg>
<seg id=13> When asked whether the sex scandal of President Clinton would affect the relationship between China and the USA, </seg>
<seg id=14> Tang said: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=15> "I think this issue is absolutely an internal issue of the United States of America. </seg>
<seg id=16> I never thought this would impose any effect on the development of Sino-US relations. </seg>
<seg id=17> President Clinton himself has made important and valuable contributions in promoting the relationship between China and the United States of America. We will not forget his contributions. </seg>
<seg id=18> In the name of Chinese Foreign Minister as well as myself, I am sincerely expecting the Sino-US relations can continue to make substantial and sustainable steps forward on the basis of three Joint Communiques and the Joint Statement by the Leaders of our two countries. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=19> The Chinese government has always been signifying that Taiwan is a province of China and Taiwan issue is the internal issue of China. </seg>
<seg id=20> Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan repeatedly talked about the Taiwan issue on many public occasions while attending the UN General Assembly and visiting Washington D. C. this time. </seg>
<seg id=21> When Tang was asked At the press conference what was the major barrier to the Sino-US strategic partnership. He said as follows: </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=22> "I think we have talked about this many times. In this regard, we need to pay particular attention to appropriately handling the Taiwan issue. </seg>
<seg id=23> Because the Taiwan issue is the most sensitive and practical issue in Sino-US relations. </seg>
</p>
